give him an alibi.

768
00:30:39.990 --> 00:30:42.270
But I couldn't do that.

769
00:30:42.300 --> 00:30:45.170
I liked the captain.

770
00:30:45.270 --> 00:30:49.290
but I couldn't risk
losing everything I have.

771
00:30:49.330 --> 00:30:51.750
not for anyone.

772
00:30:51.780 --> 00:30:53.810
- How did Braddock respond?

773
00:30:53.840 --> 00:30:57.140
- He got mad.

774
00:30:57.180 --> 00:31:01.390
Reminded me he saved my life.
which is true. but--

775
00:31:01.460 --> 00:31:03.160
- To be clear.
did Braddock confess

776
00:31:03.220 --> 00:31:05.160
to stealing the necklace?

777
00:31:05.190 --> 00:31:08.980
- Not at first. but then

778
00:31:09.010 --> 00:31:11.020
he told me he got MS
from breathing in debris

779
00:31:11.120 --> 00:31:13.330
at Ground Zero.
but the Health Fund

780
00:31:13.360 --> 00:31:16.000
wouldn't cover the cost
of his treatment.

781
00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:19.160
Said it wasn't fair
and that insurance

782
00:31:19.200 --> 00:31:21.370
had reimbursed
the store anyway.

783
00:31:21.500 --> 00:31:24.010
that it was a victimless crime.

784
00:31:24.110 --> 00:31:26.840
I guess he felt like
he was owed something.

785
00:31:26.870 --> 00:31:28.500
- But you didn't budge?

786
00:31:28.530 --> 00:31:29.850
- No.

787
00:31:29.980 --> 00:31:34.510
Then he started waving
this file in my face.

788
00:31:34.550 --> 00:31:36.190
He said he could
make it look like

789
00:31:36.290 --> 00:31:39.190
it was me who took
the necklace.

790
00:31:39.330 --> 00:31:42.200
It would be his word
against mine.

791
00:31:42.260 --> 00:31:45.570
I didn't know what to do.

792
00:31:45.670 --> 00:31:48.890
so I tried to leave
and go upstairs.

793
00:31:49.030 --> 00:31:51.170
But Braddock grabbed me.

794
00:31:51.270 --> 00:31:53.570
and we started shoving.

795
00:31:53.670 --> 00:31:57.280
And then he grabbed
the Halligan. and--and I--

796
00:31:57.340 --> 00:32:00.380
♪ ♪

797
00:32:00.480 --> 00:32:03.850
I wrestled it away. and...

798
00:32:03.950 --> 00:32:08.120
then he came at me again.

799
00:32:12.410 --> 00:32:14.380
- That's when you hit him.

800
00:32:14.410 --> 00:32:16.930
- Yes.

801
00:32:17.030 --> 00:32:21.060
I wish I could take it back.

802
00:32:21.090 --> 00:32:23.100
And I'm sorry.

803
00:32:25.930 --> 00:32:29.230
But he gave me no choice.

804
00:32:29.270 --> 00:32:33.910
I thought he was
going to kill me.

805
00:32:33.980 --> 00:32:36.780
- So why not just say that
to the police?

806
00:32:36.880 --> 00:32:41.150
- I panicked.
I knew he was right.

807
00:32:41.220 --> 00:32:44.160
No one would believe
the truth coming from me.

808
00:32:44.220 --> 00:32:48.290
So I grabbed the file
and I stashed it with my stuff.

809
00:32:48.420 --> 00:32:51.500
And then I opened the back door

810
00:32:51.570 --> 00:32:54.270
to make it look like
someone ran out.

811
00:32:54.370 --> 00:32:58.070
and I called 911.

812
00:32:58.170 --> 00:33:02.610
I know lying was wrong.

813
00:33:02.710 --> 00:33:04.390
but I was scared.

814
00:33:06.070 --> 00:33:08.480
And I thought I had no choice.

815
00:33:12.490 --> 00:33:14.990
- Thank you.

816
00:33:15.090 --> 00:33:17.320
Nothing further. Your Honor.

817
00:33:20.090 --> 00:33:22.730
- Court will stand in recess
until tomorrow.

818
00:33:22.760 --> 00:33:25.200
We'll reconvene at 9:00 a.m.

819
00:33:25.270 --> 00:33:28.100
- He was convincing.
especially when he said

820
00:33:28.130 --> 00:33:30.940
no one would believe
the truth coming from him.

821
00:33:30.970 --> 00:33:32.810
- Well. now we get to ask why.

822
00:33:32.940 --> 00:33:36.440
- He opened the door. and
now we get to walk through it.

823
00:33:36.510 --> 00:33:39.880
- Thank you.

824
00:33:39.950 --> 00:33:42.140
Peralta was right.

825
00:33:42.170 --> 00:33:45.320
I just spoke with
Braddock's neurologist.

826
00:33:45.350 --> 00:33:46.990
A few months before the murder.

827
00:33:47.120 --> 00:33:50.460
he was diagnosed with
early-stage multiple sclerosis.

828
00:33:50.490 --> 00:33:52.660
- Really?
- Yeah.

829
00:33:52.730 --> 00:33:55.200
In his estimation.
it was environmental.

830
00:33:55.300 --> 00:33:57.660
a result of Braddock's work
at Ground Zero.

831
00:33:57.690 --> 00:34:00.430
But since the science
isn't there to prove it yet.

832
00:34:00.500 --> 00:34:02.340
the health fund
denied him benefits.

833
00:34:02.400 --> 00:34:05.670
- And yet no one else
in Braddock's life

834
00:34:05.710 --> 00:34:08.510
knew about this--
his wife. his friends?

835
00:34:08.610 --> 00:34:10.670
- He must have chosen
to keep it a secret.

836
00:34:10.700 --> 00:34:12.510
-
And so he kept it from

837
00:34:12.610 --> 00:34:18.020
everyone in his life
but Peralta?

838
00:34:18.080 --> 00:34:20.850
Which means--

839
00:34:20.920 --> 00:34:23.720
that means there's some merit
to Peralta's version of events

840
00:34:23.850 --> 00:34:26.390
the night of the murder.

841
00:34:26.490 --> 00:34:29.350
- Yeah. I suppose.

842
00:34:29.380 --> 00:34:31.890
But he could have
found out before.

843
00:34:31.990 --> 00:34:35.390
Or he could have overheard
a conversation with a doctor.

844
00:34:35.530 --> 00:34:37.860
might even seen a medical bill.

845
00:34:42.510 --> 00:34:45.400
You good?

846
00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:48.750
- Yeah. fine.
I'll see you tomorrow.

847
00:35:00.430 --> 00:35:02.360
- I didn't know you had
a bottle stashed in here.

848
00:35:02.460 --> 00:35:05.100
- It literally
just came with the office.

849
00:35:08.080 --> 00:35:09.690
- Something bothering you?

850
00:35:11.370 --> 00:35:13.900
-

851
00:35:13.930 --> 00:35:17.540
The idea that Braddock
stole the necklace

852
00:35:17.640 --> 00:35:21.900
has never made any sense.

853
00:35:21.930 --> 00:35:25.620
But now we know he was staring
down a mountain of medical debt

854
00:35:25.720 --> 00:35:28.090
as a result of his service.

855
00:35:28.190 --> 00:35:30.740
- Doesn't mean
he committed grand larceny.

856
00:35:30.770 --> 00:35:32.790
- No.

857
00:35:32.890 --> 00:35:37.130
But earlier today.

858
00:35:37.260 --> 00:35:39.770
Peralta's wife asked me why
I didn't believe his story.

859
00:35:39.800 --> 00:35:43.070
And if I'm being honest.

860
00:35:43.100 --> 00:35:46.740
it's because I knew about
his prior convictions.

861
00:35:46.770 --> 00:35:49.280
- He also lied to the police.

862
00:35:49.310 --> 00:35:51.780
- Yeah. it's a thing
a person might do.

863
00:35:51.850 --> 00:35:54.280
knowing how we tend
to treat ex-felons.

864
00:35:54.350 --> 00:35:56.930
- That's true.

865
00:35:56.970 --> 00:35:59.290
But we both know
the best predictor

866
00:35:59.420 --> 00:36:01.450
of future behavior
is past behavior.

867
00:36:01.550 --> 00:36:04.650
- And other than
the two felonies years ago.

868
00:36:04.780 --> 00:36:08.130
he's been a solid citizen.
he was a model inmate. parolee.

869
00:36:08.190 --> 00:36:09.560
He mentored at-risk kids.

870
00:36:09.600 --> 00:36:12.160
He was making the most
of his second chance.

871
00:36:12.290 --> 00:36:14.830
That's past behavior.

872
00:36:14.930 --> 00:36:17.960
That's recent past behavior.

873
00:36:18.000 --> 00:36:21.310
which is more predictive
than distant past behavior.

874
00:36:21.370 --> 00:36:26.480
And I didn't take any of that
into consideration.

875
00:36:26.580 --> 00:36:29.920
- You think Peralta
is telling the truth.

876
00:36:29.980 --> 00:36:32.120
- Not sure.
How can we know for sure?

877
00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:34.990
- You can't.
We weren't there.

878
00:36:35.020 --> 00:36:36.820
All we can do
is present the evidence

879
00:36:36.860 --> 00:36:38.810
and let the jury decide.
- Right.

880
00:36:38.840 --> 00:36:40.390
We present
the prior convictions.

881
00:36:40.460 --> 00:36:42.200
We paint him out to be
an inveterate criminal

882
00:36:42.300 --> 00:36:44.330
and let the jury nail his ass
to the cross.

883
00:36:44.400 --> 00:36:45.930
- Look. this job would
be easy if we knew

884
00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:48.530
what really happened.
but we don't.

885
00:36:48.630 --> 00:36:50.530
We usually never do.

886
00:36:50.660 --> 00:36:53.200
So we follow the law.

887
00:36:53.300 --> 00:36:56.840
We play every card we have.
just like the defense does.

888
00:36:56.880 --> 00:36:58.950
And we let the 12 people who
don't have a horse in the race

889
00:36:58.980 --> 00:37:00.380
make the decision.

890
00:37:00.480 --> 00:37:03.170
- Yeah. I get it.
Trust me.

891
00:37:03.200 --> 00:37:06.620
But...

892
00:37:06.690 --> 00:37:10.340
if every sentence
is a life sentence.

893
00:37:10.370 --> 00:37:13.340
what's the point
of rehabilitation?

894
00:37:16.500 --> 00:37:19.030
- Okay.

895
00:37:19.130 --> 00:37:22.240
If you feel this strongly.
dismiss the case.

896
00:37:25.340 --> 00:37:27.340
- I can't do that.
It's like I said.

897
00:37:27.410 --> 00:37:31.210
I just--I don't know.

898
00:37:31.310 --> 00:37:35.450
- Then you have to do
what you have to do.

899
00:37:35.520 --> 00:37:42.510
♪ ♪

900
00:37:42.580 --> 00:37:45.490
-

901
00:37:45.530 --> 00:37:52.100
♪ ♪

902
00:38:04.880 --> 00:38:09.570
Mr. Peralta. you testified
that you lied to the police

903
00:38:09.600 --> 00:38:13.520
because you knew that no one
would believe your story.

904
00:38:13.590 --> 00:38:15.740
Why wouldn't they believe you?

905
00:38:15.770 --> 00:38:17.220
- I don't know.

906
00:38:17.320 --> 00:38:19.460
- Is it because you have
a prior conviction

907
00:38:19.590 --> 00:38:21.090
for aggravated assault?
- Objection.

908
00:38:21.130 --> 00:38:22.950
- I'm responding to direct
testimony. Your Honor.

909
00:38:23.090 --> 00:38:24.760
- Objection overruled.

910
00:38:24.800 --> 00:38:28.300
- Or was it because of your
prior conviction for burglary?

911
00:38:33.910 --> 00:38:38.270
- Yes.
I've served time in prison.

912
00:38:40.640 --> 00:38:43.480
I've done things in my past
that I'm not proud of.

913
00:38:43.620 --> 00:38:47.600
And I take full responsibility
for my actions.

914
00:38:47.640 --> 00:38:51.770
I paid my debt to society.

915
00:38:51.810 --> 00:38:53.960
But once you've done time.

916
00:38:54.090 --> 00:38:56.620
there's no such thing
as benefit of the doubt.

917
00:39:02.600 --> 00:39:04.000
- Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury.

918
00:39:04.130 --> 00:39:06.830
these are photographs
of Mateo Ortiz.

919
00:39:06.970 --> 00:39:11.180
These were taken shortly after
the defendant assaulted him

920
00:39:11.310 --> 00:39:13.280
for signaling a police officer

921
00:39:13.310 --> 00:39:15.270
when he caught
Mr. Peralta shoplifting.

922
00:39:15.340 --> 00:39:17.380
- It was a long time ago.

923
00:39:17.450 --> 00:39:22.120
I was 15. an angry kid
in a bad neighborhood.

924
00:39:22.160 --> 00:39:23.990
I got mixed up with
the wrong people.

925
00:39:24.060 --> 00:39:26.690
- You were 24 when you
were convicted of burglary.

926
00:39:26.790 --> 00:39:28.290
And you did it again.
didn't you?

927
00:39:28.390 --> 00:39:30.030
But your captain
figured it out.

928
00:39:30.130 --> 00:39:31.520
He confronted you.
- No.

929
00:39:31.620 --> 00:39:33.830
- Mr. Peralta. isn't it true
that you lied to the police

930
00:39:33.870 --> 00:39:36.340
because you are the one
who stole the necklace?

931
00:39:36.400 --> 00:39:38.030
Then you murdered
Captain Braddock

932
00:39:38.160 --> 00:39:40.510
to keep him from reporting you.

933
00:39:40.640 --> 00:39:46.410
That the same man
who did this to Mateo Ortiz

934
00:39:46.480 --> 00:39:50.470
did this to Clint Braddock.

935
00:39:55.490 --> 00:39:58.390
Nothing to say. Mr. Peralta?

936
00:39:58.520 --> 00:40:00.360
-
What's the point?

937
00:40:00.460 --> 00:40:01.830
- Your Honor.
please instruct Mr. Peralta

938
00:40:01.900 --> 00:40:04.230
to address the court.

939
00:40:04.330 --> 00:40:07.850
- I said. what's the point?

940
00:40:07.880 --> 00:40:09.370
I've already told you
the truth.

941
00:40:09.470 --> 00:40:12.860
and you've already decided
that you don't believe me.

942
00:40:16.010 --> 00:40:17.980
♪ ♪

943
00:40:18.010 --> 00:40:20.710
- Nothing further.

944
00:40:20.850 --> 00:40:27.880
♪ ♪

945
00:40:33.580 --> 00:40:37.060
- Madam Foreperson.
has the jury reached a verdict?

946
00:40:37.100 --> 00:40:38.500
- We have. Your Honor.

947
00:40:38.560 --> 00:40:41.500
In the charge of murder
in the second degree.

948
00:40:41.530 --> 00:40:46.760
we find the defendant.
Diego Peralta. guilty.

949
00:40:46.860 --> 00:40:49.390
-

950
00:40:49.430 --> 00:40:50.910
- I didn't do this. Ruby.
- I know.

951
00:40:51.040 --> 00:40:52.230
- I need you to know that.
- I know. mi amor.

952
00:40:52.260 --> 00:40:53.250
- I need you to know that.

953
00:40:53.350 --> 00:40:54.550
And Anthony.
you be strong. okay?

954
00:40:54.610 --> 00:40:55.940
I love you.

955
00:40:56.070 --> 00:40:57.910
I love you more than anything.
You make sure he knows that.

956
00:40:57.940 --> 00:40:59.090
You make sure he knows
that I'm innocent.

957
00:40:59.190 --> 00:41:00.350
- I promise.
- Tell him. please.

958
00:41:00.390 --> 00:41:01.610
- I promise.
- Tell her.

959
00:41:01.750 --> 00:41:02.820
And you tell our baby.

960
00:41:02.890 --> 00:41:05.430
- I will.
- You tell her.

961
00:41:05.530 --> 00:41:07.410
-

962
00:41:10.400 --> 00:41:17.470
♪ ♪

963
00:41:28.580 --> 00:41:35.660
♪ ♪
